<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bryan | Philosophy & Engineering</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --portal-blue: #00aaff;
            --portal-orange: #ff9900;
            --dark: #202020;
            --glass: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
        }
        body { 
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; 
            background: #e0e0e0; 
            color: #333; 
            margin: 0; 
            padding: 40px; 
        }
        .container { max-width: 850px; margin: 0 auto; background: var(--glass); padding: 40px; border-radius: 15px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
        header { border-left: 8px solid var(--portal-blue); padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
        h1 { margin: 0; font-size: 3em; letter-spacing: -1px; }
        .tagline { color: var(--portal-orange); font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; }
        
        section { margin-bottom: 30px; }
        h2 { border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 10px; font-size: 1.4em; }
        
        .hobby-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
        .card { background: #fff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #eee; }
        
        .highlight { font-weight: bold; color: var(--portal-blue); }
        .quote { font-style: italic; color: #666; border-left: 3px solid #ccc; padding-left: 15px; margin: 20px 0; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <header>
        <h1>BRYAN</h1>
        <div class="tagline">National Quemoy University | Electrical Engineering</div>
        <p>Combining the <strong>Logic of Philosophy</strong> with the <strong>Precision of Engineering</strong>.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>The Philosophical Engineer</h2>
        <p>I view Engineering through a philosophical lens: as the study of how logical structures manifest in the physical world. My goal is to apply rigorous analytical thinking to circuit design and power systems.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Interactive Logic & Gaming</h2>
        <div class="card" style="border-right: 5px solid var(--portal-orange);">
            <p><strong>Portal 1 & 2 (Valve):</strong> I am fascinated by these games not just for the story, but for their mastery of <span class="highlight">Spatial Reasoning</span> and <span class="highlight">Physics-Based Problem Solving</span>. Analyzing how portals conserve momentum is a great mental exercise for understanding complex system inputs and outputs.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="hobby-grid">
        <section class="card">
            <h2>Hardware Skills</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Computer Repair:</strong> Logical diagnosis and component replacement.</li>
                <li><strong>System Optimization:</strong> Balancing performance and efficiency.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Personal Hobbies</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Fitness:</strong> Human-system maintenance and discipline.</li>
                <li><strong>Inquiry:</strong> Engaging in deep discussions on any topic "under the sun."</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </div>

    <section>
        <p style="text-align: center; color: #888; font-size: 0.9em;">
            <em>"We do what we must because we can."</em> — Aperture Science
        </p>
    </section>
</div>

</body>
</html>
